<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="549" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,438,1147]" box="[151,751,438,463]" pageId="8" pageNumber="549">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,438,463]" pageId="8" pageNumber="549">Description.</emphasis>
Length (including wings): male 
<quantity box="[664,747,439,463]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.9" pageId="8" pageNumber="549" unit="mm" value="2.9">2.9mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,438,1147]" pageId="8" pageNumber="549">
Crown and lower part of face ochraceous, face dorsad of antennal bases ochraceous with brown tinge (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1541,1563]" captionTargetBox="[319,1266,368,1519]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[302,1284,363,1519]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Busonia micrata sp. nov. A, habitus, dorsal view; B, habitus, lateral view; C, head and thorax, dorsal view; D, face. Busonia serrata sp. nov. E, habitus, dorsal view; F, habitus, lateral view; G, head and thorax, dorsal view; H, face. Busonia albilateralis Maldonado-Capriles I, habitus, dorsal view; J, habitus, lateral view; K, head and thorax, dorsal view; L, face." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241682/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="549">
Figs. 
<number box="[151,164,511,535]" pageId="8" pageNumber="549" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
G, H). Pronotum ochraceous, lateral areas more brownish. Mesoscutum and scutellum light chocolate brown, basal triangles darker. Forewing hyaline with light brown tinge, broad band along costa except for a subapical triangle, dark brown (
<figureCitation box="[408,480,582,607]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1541,1563]" captionTargetBox="[319,1266,368,1519]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[302,1284,363,1519]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Busonia micrata sp. nov. A, habitus, dorsal view; B, habitus, lateral view; C, head and thorax, dorsal view; D, face. Busonia serrata sp. nov. E, habitus, dorsal view; F, habitus, lateral view; G, head and thorax, dorsal view; H, face. Busonia albilateralis Maldonado-Capriles I, habitus, dorsal view; J, habitus, lateral view; K, head and thorax, dorsal view; L, face." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241682/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="549">
Fig. 
<number box="[465,480,583,607]" pageId="8" pageNumber="549" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
F). Mesepimeron dark brown. Legs pale ochraceous, hind leg spinulation reddish brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,438,1147]" pageId="8" pageNumber="549">
Male genitalia. Pygofer with height more than length, dorsal margin with posterior dorsally projected lobe. Appendage of segment X slender directed ventrally and posteriorly, in posterior view not crossing over each other. Subgenital plate narrow, long, with a few hair-like long setae; about as long as posterior margin of pygofer (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1874,1896]" captionTargetBox="[172,1421,380,1838]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,359,1851]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 5. Busonia serrata sp. nov. A, male pygofer, anal tube and subgenital plate, lateral view; B, connective, ventral view; C, style, lateral view; D, aedeagus, ventral view; E, aedeagus, lateral view. Busonia albilateralis Maldonado-Capriles F, aedeagus, ventral view; G, aedeagus, lateral view; H, male pygofer, anal tube and subgenital plate, lateral view; I, connective, ventral view; J, style, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241685/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="549">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,165,762,787]" pageId="8" pageNumber="549" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
A). Connective with two arms square, manubrium slender, central lobe broad and lamellate. Style tooth on ventral margin nearer to basal apex than to distal apex, with row of sparsely distributed setae. Aedeagus with atrial region as long as shaft, posterior rim of atrium broad, almost as broad as long, shaft curved anteriorly, with gonopore all along its length projecting beyond curvature of the shaft in lateral view; margins of gonopore finely serrate (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1874,1896]" captionTargetBox="[172,1421,380,1838]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,359,1851]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 5. Busonia serrata sp. nov. A, male pygofer, anal tube and subgenital plate, lateral view; B, connective, ventral view; C, style, lateral view; D, aedeagus, ventral view; E, aedeagus, lateral view. Busonia albilateralis Maldonado-Capriles F, aedeagus, ventral view; G, aedeagus, lateral view; H, male pygofer, anal tube and subgenital plate, lateral view; I, connective, ventral view; J, style, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241685/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="549">
Figs. 
<number box="[151,165,906,931]" pageId="8" pageNumber="549" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
D, E).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1249,942,967]" pageId="8" pageNumber="549" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,438,1147]" box="[199,1249,942,967]" pageId="8" pageNumber="549">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,942,967]" pageId="8" pageNumber="549">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet refers to the finely serrate margins of the aedeagal gonopore.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
