<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="549" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,438,1147]" pageId="8" pageNumber="549">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1050,1075]" pageId="8" pageNumber="549">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[323,504,1051,1074]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Busonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="549" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serrata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[323,504,1051,1074]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="549">Busonia serrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[512,602,1050,1075]" pageId="8" pageNumber="549" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[512,602,1050,1075]" pageId="8" pageNumber="549">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
can at once be distinguished from all other known species of 
<taxonomicName box="[1308,1400,1051,1074]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Busonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="549" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1308,1400,1051,1074]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="549">Busonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the finely serrate gonopore margin. It also differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[768,884,1087,1110]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Busonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="549" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="curvata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[768,785,1087,1110]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="549">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[799,884,1087,1110]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="549">curvata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[891,981,1086,1111]" pageId="8" pageNumber="549" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[891,981,1086,1111]" pageId="8" pageNumber="549">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
(see below) by the aedeagal shaft lateral margin not curved anteriorly in ventral view.
</paragraph>
